LAGOS – Controversial Nollywood actor and politician, Yul Edochie has lamented the alarming rate of kidney failure cases in Nigeria. According to the veteran actor who has currently been in the news for the wrong reasons, the rate at which youths in their 20’s suffer kidney failure has become worrisome. However, he urged medical practitioners in Nigeria to educate Nigerians on the factors responsible for this ailment so as to forestall its prevention. He wrote on his twitter handle, “Kidney failure has become rampant in our society today. Even young people in their 20’s are dying of it. To our Doctors & medical practitioners in the house, please help. What are the causes of kidney failure? Are there early detection signs so it can be checked?” See tweet below;